<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-13T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-13T10:00:00-05:00" n="787" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d787">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">211.67/41: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-13T17:00:00+02:00">February 13, 1934—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 13—2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>7. Department’s No. 18, February 9, 3 p.m. Extradition Treaty
                                presented National Assembly November 25 and will be ratified during
                                next session beginning March 1st.<note n="53" xml:id="d787fn53">Ratified by the President of the United States, February 21,
                                    1934; ratified by Turkey, May 8, 1934; ratifications exchanged
                                    at Ankara, June 18, 1934; proclaimed by the President of the
                                    United States, August 18, 1934. Department of State Treaty
                                    Series No. 872.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>